{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Qnie8V1XPejp4oRJSJVnFD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QenzPBJw7dX5dvnCT1L6J8","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# RabbitMQ Cluster Change / Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-16  \n**Cluster namespace:** karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-0f5d4e03-cluster-a  \n**Status:** PLAN ONLY — no changes applied; live cluster unchanged\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster State (baseline snapshot)\n\n### 1.1 Cluster topology\n\n| Item | Value |\n|---|---|\n| RabbitMQ version | 3.12.14 (out of support) |\n| Erlang/OTP | 25.3.2.15 (erts-13.2.2.11) |\n| Container image | `rabbitmq:3.12-management` |\n| Node count | 3 disk nodes (rabbitmq-0, rabbitmq-1, rabbitmq-2) |\n| Cluster partition handling | `pause_minority` |\n| Queue master locator | `min-masters` |\n| TLS listeners | AMQP/TLS on 5671 (verify_peer, peer cert not required) |\n| AMQP plaintext | 5672 |\n| Management HTTP | 15672 |\n| Prometheus | 15692 (0.0.0.0) |\n\n### 1.2 Plugins enabled\n\n`rabbitmq_management`, `rabbitmq_prometheus`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s`\n(+ transitive deps: `rabbitmq_management_agent`, `rabbitmq_web_dispatch`,\n`amqp_client`, `cowboy`, `cowlib`, `accept`, `prometheus`,\n`rabbitmq_peer_discovery_common`)\n\n### 1.3 Virtual hosts\n\n| Vhost | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `/` | Default (unused — no queues, no non-admin users) |\n| `/app` | Application workload vhost |\n| `/ops` | Operations/tooling vhost |\n\n### 1.4 Users and permissions\n\n| User | Tags | Vhost | configure | write | read |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `admin` | administrator | `/`, `/app`, `/ops` | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n| `app-user` | management | `/app` | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n| `ops-user` | management | `/ops` | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n\nGuest user login is disabled for non-loopback addresses (`loopback_users.guest = false`).\n\n### 1.5 Queues\n\n| Vhost | Queue | Type | Durable | Auto-delete | Arguments |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `/app` | `app-queue` | classic | true | false | `x-queue-type: classic` |\n| `/ops` | `ops-queue` | classic | true | false | `x-queue-type: classic` |\n\nNo queues exist in the default (`/`) vhost.\n\n### 1.6 Exchanges and bindings\n\nBoth `/app` and `/ops` carry only the seven built-in AMQP exchanges (default\ndirect, `amq.direct`, `amq.topic`, `amq.fanout`, `amq.headers`, `amq.match`,\n`amq.rabbitmq.trace`). No custom exchanges are declared.\n\nBindings:\n- `/app`: default exchange → `app-queue` (routing key `app-queue`)\n- `/ops`: default exchange → `ops-queue` (routing key `ops-queue`)\n\n### 1.7 Policies\n\n| Vhost | Policy | Pattern | Apply-to | Definition | Priority |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `/app` | `ha-all` | `.*` | queues | `{\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"}` | 0 |\n\nNo policies exist on `/ops` or `/`.\n\n**Note:** `ha-mode: all` is a classic mirrored queue policy. This policy class\nis deprecated in RabbitMQ 3.x and **removed in RabbitMQ 4.0**. It cannot be\napplied to quorum queues and provides no benefit when the queue type is set to\n`quorum` (which has built-in replication). This is the primary migration concern.\n\n### 1.8 Feature flags (all enabled)\n\n`classic_mirrored_queue_version`, `classic_queue_type_delivery_support`,\n`direct_exchange_routing_v2`, `drop_unroutable_metric`, `empty_basic_get_metric`,\n`feature_flags_v2`, `implicit_default_bindings`, `listener_records_in_ets`,\n`maintenance_mode_status`, `quorum_queue`, `restart_streams`, `stream_queue`,\n`stream_sac_coordinator_unblock_group`, `stream_single_active_consumer`,\n`tracking_records_in_ets`, `user_limits`, `virtual_host_metadata`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Upgrade and Migration Plan\n\n### 2.1 Target versions\n\n| Component | Current | Target | Rationale |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| RabbitMQ | 3.12.14 | 3.13.x (latest 3.13 patch) | Last supported 3.x series; stepping-stone before 4.0 |\n| Erlang/OTP | 25.3.2.15 | 26.x (compatible with RabbitMQ 3.13) | Required by 3.13 |\n| Container image | `rabbitmq:3.12-management` | `rabbitmq:3.13-management` | Same image family |\n\nA direct jump to 4.0 is blocked by the `ha-all` classic mirrored queue policy\n(4.0 drops classic mirroring entirely). The 3.12 → 3.13 upgrade is the required\nstepping-stone to enable all 3.13 feature flags before attempting 4.0.\n\n### 2.2 Pre-upgrade checklist (perform before change window)\n\n1. **Snapshot current configuration** — export definitions via the management\n   API (`GET /api/definitions`) and store in a versioned backup (ConfigMap or\n   object store). This is idempotent and safe to do at any time.\n\n2. **Review `ha-all` policy impact** — `app-queue` in `/app` is currently a\n   classic mirrored queue because of the `ha-all` policy. Before upgrading to\n   3.13 (and certainly before 4.0), this queue must be migrated to a quorum\n   queue. Assess whether the application can tolerate a brief queue recreation\n   (quorum queues cannot be created in-place from classic queues).\n\n3. **Verify consumer/producer compatibility** — `app-producer` pod is currently\n   in `CrashLoopBackOff`. Diagnose and resolve this before the change window to\n   ensure post-upgrade validation is not confounded by a pre-existing application\n   fault.\n\n4. **Confirm Erlang 26 image availability** — validate that\n   `rabbitmq:3.13-management` is reachable from the cluster's image registry and\n   contains Erlang 26.\n\n5. **Review `ssl_options.fail_if_no_peer_cert = false`** — mutual TLS is\n   currently optional for clients. Decide whether to enforce it (`true`) as part\n   of this change window or defer.\n\n### 2.3 Migration steps (change window, ordered)\n\n#### Step 1 — Migrate `app-queue` from classic-mirrored to quorum type\n\nClassic mirrored queues are deprecated in 3.12 and removed in 4.0. The `ha-all`\npolicy on `/app` currently mirrors `app-queue` across all three nodes.\n\n```bash\n# 1a. Drain the queue (coordinate with app-producer / app-client to quiesce)\n# 1b. Delete the existing classic queue\nrabbitmqctl delete_queue app-queue --vhost /app\n\n# 1c. Re-declare app-queue as quorum type\nrabbitmqctl declare_queue --vhost /app --name app-queue \\\n  --type quorum --durable true\n\n# 1d. Remove the now-redundant ha-all policy\nrabbitmqctl clear_policy ha-all --vhost /app\n```\n\nAfter this step, `app-queue` uses quorum replication natively (Raft-based,\nmajority quorum on 3 nodes) — no mirroring policy needed.\n\n#### Step 2 — Rolling StatefulSet upgrade to RabbitMQ 3.13\n\nPerform a rolling upgrade one pod at a time. With `pause_minority` partition\nhandling and 3 nodes, the cluster remains operational as long as 2/3 nodes are\nup.\n\n```bash\n# Update image in the StatefulSet\nkubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-0f5d4e03-cluster-a \\\n  set image statefulset/rabbitmq rabbitmq=rabbitmq:3.13-management\n\n# The StatefulSet will roll pods one at a time (rabbitmq-2 → rabbitmq-1 → rabbitmq-0)\n# Monitor each pod restart:\nkubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-0f5d4e03-cluster-a \\\n  rollout status statefulset/rabbitmq\n```\n\nAfter each pod rejoins: `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` — confirm node is\n`Running` and no alarms.\n\n#### Step 3 — Enable new 3.13 feature flags\n\nAfter all three nodes are on 3.13:\n\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n```\n\nThis enables any flags new in 3.13 that were not present in 3.12, and is\nrequired before a subsequent upgrade to 4.0.\n\n#### Step 4 — Post-upgrade validation\n\n```bash\n# Cluster health\nrabbitmqctl cluster_status\nrabbitmq-diagnostics check_running\nrabbitmq-diagnostics check_alarms\n\n# Queue integrity\nrabbitmqctl list_queues --vhost /app name type state leader_node members\nrabbitmqctl list_queues --vhost /ops name type state\n\n# Policy cleanup confirmation (ha-all should be absent)\nrabbitmqctl list_policies --vhost /app\n```\n\nConfirm `app-queue` type is `quorum`, leader is elected, and all 3 nodes are\nmembers. Confirm `ops-queue` remains `classic` (no migration needed; `/ops`\ncarries no HA policy).\n\n#### Step 5 — Application reconnection validation\n\nRestart `app-producer` and `app-client` deployments and confirm messages flow\nthrough `app-queue` end-to-end. Verify Prometheus metrics are scraped\n(port 15692) and the management UI responds on 15672.\n\n### 2.4 Deferred items (out of scope for this window)\n\n| Item | Recommendation |\n|---|---|\n| `ops-queue` type | Evaluate migrating to quorum for consistency; currently classic with no HA policy, so single-node loss loses the queue. |\n| TLS mutual auth | Set `ssl_options.fail_if_no_peer_cert = true` after issuing client certs to app-producer / app-client. |\n| `queue_master_locator = min-masters` | Deprecated in 3.x; has no effect on quorum queues. Remove from config after queue migration is complete. |\n| Upgrade to 4.0 | Schedule a follow-on window after 3.13 is stable in production. Requires all classic mirrored queues to be eliminated first (done in Step 1). |\n| `app-producer` CrashLoopBackOff | Unrelated to the upgrade but must be resolved before the change window to enable post-upgrade validation. |\n\n### 2.5 Rollback procedure\n\nIf the StatefulSet upgrade must be rolled back before all nodes are updated:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-0f5d4e03-cluster-a \\\n  set image statefulset/rabbitmq rabbitmq=rabbitmq:3.12-management\nkubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-0f5d4e03-cluster-a \\\n  rollout status statefulset/rabbitmq\n```\n\nRabbitMQ 3.13 → 3.12 downgrade is supported only if the 3.13-only feature flags\nhave **not** been enabled (Step 3). If Step 3 has already been applied, rollback\nis not possible without restoring the Mnesia/Raft data from the pre-upgrade\nsnapshot — this is why the definitions backup in the pre-upgrade checklist is\ncritical.\n\nThe quorum queue created in Step 1 is compatible with both 3.12 and 3.13, so\nthe queue type migration does not affect rollback feasibility.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Risk Summary\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|\n| Classic mirrored queue removal in 4.0 | High | Step 1 (queue migration) must complete before any 4.0 upgrade attempt |\n| `app-producer` already failing pre-upgrade | Medium | Diagnose and fix before the change window |\n| Brief queue unavailability during queue re-declaration (Step 1) | Medium | Coordinate quiesce window with application teams; quorum queue declares atomically |\n| Erlang 26 behavior differences | Low | No application-level Erlang interaction; risk is framework-internal only |\n| Feature flag enablement is irreversible | High | Do not run Step 3 until rollback decision point has passed |\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":542,"cache_read_input_tokens":36586,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":542},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"22aadd6e-19b4-4a96-bb35-59be6d64c0a7","uuid":"20a74bde-b729-4d70-9d35-7fe85367ad57","request_id":"req_011Cc76TGvVyE6ktXoBob49R"}
