{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SzbW35d3paACiEKJUsuptp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01ETvixfjExt7TpDnQt6ifwf","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /tmp/plan.md << 'PLANEOF'\n# RabbitMQ Cluster Change / Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-16\n**Cluster namespace:** karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-0f5d4e03-cluster-a\n**Status:** PLAN ONLY — no changes applied; live cluster unchanged\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster State (baseline snapshot)\n\n### 1.1 Cluster topology\n\n| Item | Value |\n|---|---|\n| RabbitMQ version | 3.12.14 (out of support) |\n| Erlang/OTP | 25.3.2.15 (erts-13.2.2.11) |\n| Container image | `rabbitmq:3.12-management` |\n| Node count | 3 disk nodes (rabbitmq-0, rabbitmq-1, rabbitmq-2) |\n| Cluster partition handling | `pause_minority` |\n| Queue master locator | `min-masters` |\n| TLS listeners | AMQP/TLS on 5671 (verify_peer, peer cert not required) |\n| AMQP plaintext | 5672 |\n| Management HTTP | 15672 |\n| Prometheus | 15692 (0.0.0.0) |\n\n### 1.2 Plugins enabled\n\n`rabbitmq_management`, `rabbitmq_prometheus`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s`\n(+ transitive deps: `rabbitmq_management_agent`, `rabbitmq_web_dispatch`,\n`amqp_client`, `cowboy`, `cowlib`, `accept`, `prometheus`,\n`rabbitmq_peer_discovery_common`)\n\n### 1.3 Virtual hosts\n\n| Vhost | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `/` | Default (unused — no queues, no non-admin users) |\n| `/app` | Application workload vhost |\n| `/ops` | Operations/tooling vhost |\n\n### 1.4 Users and permissions\n\n| User | Tags | Vhost | configure | write | read |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `admin` | administrator | `/`, `/app`, `/ops` | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n| `app-user` | management | `/app` | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n| `ops-user` | management | `/ops` | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n\nGuest user login is disabled for non-loopback addresses (`loopback_users.guest = false`).\n\n### 1.5 Queues\n\n| Vhost | Queue | Type | Durable | Auto-delete | Arguments |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `/app` | `app-queue` | classic | true | false | `x-queue-type: classic` |\n| `/ops` | `ops-queue` | classic | true | false | `x-queue-type: classic` |\n\nNo queues exist in the default (`/`) vhost.\n\n### 1.6 Exchanges and bindings\n\nBoth `/app` and `/ops` carry only the seven built-in AMQP exchanges (default\ndirect, `amq.direct`, `amq.topic`, `amq.fanout`, `amq.headers`, `amq.match`,\n`amq.rabbitmq.trace`). No custom exchanges are declared.\n\nBindings:\n- `/app`: default exchange -> `app-queue` (routing key `app-queue`)\n- `/ops`: default exchange -> `ops-queue` (routing key `ops-queue`)\n\n### 1.7 Policies\n\n| Vhost | Policy | Pattern | Apply-to | Definition | Priority |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `/app` | `ha-all` | `.*` | queues | `{\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"}` | 0 |\n\nNo policies exist on `/ops` or `/`.\n\n**Note:** `ha-mode: all` is a classic mirrored queue policy. This policy class\nis deprecated in RabbitMQ 3.x and REMOVED in RabbitMQ 4.0. It cannot be applied\nto quorum queues. This is the primary migration concern before any 4.0 upgrade.\n\n### 1.8 Feature flags (all enabled)\n\n`classic_mirrored_queue_version`, `classic_queue_type_delivery_support`,\n`direct_exchange_routing_v2`, `drop_unroutable_metric`, `empty_basic_get_metric`,\n`feature_flags_v2`, `implicit_default_bindings`, `listener_records_in_ets`,\n`maintenance_mode_status`, `quorum_queue`, `restart_streams`, `stream_queue`,\n`stream_sac_coordinator_unblock_group`, `stream_single_active_consumer`,\n`tracking_records_in_ets`, `user_limits`, `virtual_host_metadata`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Upgrade and Migration Plan\n\n### 2.1 Target versions\n\n| Component | Current | Target | Rationale |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| RabbitMQ | 3.12.14 | 3.13.x (latest 3.13 patch) | Last supported 3.x series; required stepping-stone before 4.0 |\n| Erlang/OTP | 25.3.2.15 | 26.x (compatible with RabbitMQ 3.13) | Required by RabbitMQ 3.13 |\n| Container image | `rabbitmq:3.12-management` | `rabbitmq:3.13-management` | Same image family |\n\nA direct jump to 4.0 is blocked by the `ha-all` classic mirrored queue policy\n(4.0 removes classic mirroring entirely). The 3.12 -> 3.13 upgrade is the\nrequired stepping-stone to enable all 3.13 feature flags before attempting 4.0.\n\n### 2.2 Pre-upgrade checklist (perform before change window)\n\n1. **Snapshot current configuration** — export definitions via the management\n   API (`GET /api/definitions`) and store in a versioned backup (ConfigMap or\n   object store). Safe to do at any time without cluster impact.\n\n2. **Review `ha-all` policy impact** — `app-queue` in `/app` is currently a\n   classic mirrored queue because of the `ha-all` policy. Before upgrading to\n   3.13 (and certainly before 4.0), this queue must be migrated to a quorum\n   queue. Assess whether the application can tolerate a brief queue recreation\n   (quorum queues cannot be converted from classic queues in place).\n\n3. **Diagnose `app-producer` CrashLoopBackOff** — the `app-producer` pod is\n   currently failing. Resolve this before the change window so that\n   post-upgrade end-to-end validation is not confounded by a pre-existing fault.\n\n4. **Confirm Erlang 26 image availability** — validate that\n   `rabbitmq:3.13-management` is reachable from the cluster's image registry\n   and packages Erlang 26.\n\n5. **Review TLS client cert enforcement** — `ssl_options.fail_if_no_peer_cert`\n   is currently `false` (mutual TLS is optional for clients). Decide whether to\n   enforce it as part of this window or defer to a later hardening window.\n\n### 2.3 Migration steps (change window, ordered)\n\n#### Step 1 — Migrate `app-queue` from classic-mirrored to quorum type\n\nClassic mirrored queues are deprecated in 3.12 and removed in 4.0. The `ha-all`\npolicy on `/app` currently mirrors `app-queue` across all three nodes. Quorum\nqueues provide equivalent (and superior) replication via Raft without a policy.\n\n```bash\n# 1a. Quiesce app-producer and app-client (coordinate with application teams)\n\n# 1b. Delete the existing classic queue (all in-flight messages will be lost\n#     if not drained first — confirm queue depth is zero before this step)\nrabbitmqctl delete_queue app-queue --vhost /app\n\n# 1c. Re-declare app-queue as a quorum queue\nrabbitmqctl declare_queue --vhost /app --name app-queue \\\n  --type quorum --durable true\n\n# 1d. Remove the now-redundant ha-all policy\nrabbitmqctl clear_policy ha-all --vhost /app\n```\n\nAfter Step 1, `app-queue` replicates via Raft across all 3 nodes natively —\nno mirroring policy is required or meaningful.\n\n#### Step 2 — Rolling StatefulSet upgrade to RabbitMQ 3.13\n\nUpgrade one pod at a time. With `pause_minority` partition handling and 3 nodes,\nthe cluster remains available as long as 2 of 3 nodes are running.\n\n```bash\n# Update the container image\nkubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-0f5d4e03-cluster-a \\\n  set image statefulset/rabbitmq rabbitmq=rabbitmq:3.13-management\n\n# StatefulSet rolls pods in reverse ordinal order: rabbitmq-2 -> rabbitmq-1 -> rabbitmq-0\n# Monitor rollout completion\nkubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-0f5d4e03-cluster-a \\\n  rollout status statefulset/rabbitmq\n```\n\nAfter each pod rejoins the cluster, run `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` to confirm\nthe node is `Running` and no alarms are raised before proceeding to the next pod.\n\n#### Step 3 — Enable new 3.13 feature flags\n\nAfter all three nodes are running 3.13:\n\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n```\n\nThis enables any feature flags introduced in 3.13 that were absent in 3.12.\n**This step is irreversible** — once enabled, rollback to 3.12 is not possible\nwithout restoring from the pre-upgrade definitions backup.\n\n#### Step 4 — Post-upgrade validation\n\n```bash\n# Cluster health\nrabbitmqctl cluster_status\nrabbitmq-diagnostics check_running\nrabbitmq-diagnostics check_alarms\n\n# Queue integrity — confirm app-queue is quorum type with a leader\nrabbitmqctl list_queues --vhost /app name type state leader_node members\nrabbitmqctl list_queues --vhost /ops  name type state\n\n# Confirm ha-all policy is absent\nrabbitmqctl list_policies --vhost /app\n```\n\nConfirm `app-queue` type is `quorum`, a leader is elected, and all 3 nodes are\nmembers. Confirm `ops-queue` remains `classic` durable.\n\n#### Step 5 — Application reconnection validation\n\nRestart `app-producer` and `app-client` deployments and confirm messages flow\nthrough `app-queue` end-to-end. Verify:\n- Prometheus metrics scraped from port 15692\n- Management UI responding at port 15672\n- `ops-client` connected to `/ops` vhost successfully\n\n### 2.4 Deferred items (out of scope for this window)\n\n| Item | Recommendation |\n|---|---|\n| `ops-queue` type upgrade | Evaluate migrating to quorum for resilience — currently classic with no HA policy, so a single-node loss loses the queue until that node recovers. |\n| TLS mutual auth enforcement | Set `ssl_options.fail_if_no_peer_cert = true` after issuing client certs to `app-producer` and `app-client`. |\n| `queue_master_locator = min-masters` | Deprecated setting with no effect on quorum queues. Remove from `rabbitmq.conf` after queue migration is confirmed stable. |\n| Upgrade to RabbitMQ 4.0 | Schedule a follow-on window after 3.13 is stable. All classic mirrored queues must be eliminated first (accomplished by Step 1 above). |\n| `app-producer` crash investigation | Must be resolved before the change window; see pre-upgrade checklist item 3. |\n\n### 2.5 Rollback procedure\n\nIf the StatefulSet upgrade fails before all nodes are updated on 3.13 **and**\nStep 3 (feature flag enablement) has NOT been run:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-0f5d4e03-cluster-a \\\n  set image statefulset/rabbitmq rabbitmq=rabbitmq:3.12-management\nkubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-0f5d4e03-cluster-a \\\n  rollout status statefulset/rabbitmq\n```\n\nIf Step 3 has already been applied, rollback to 3.12 requires restoring the\nMnesia/Raft data volumes from the pre-upgrade snapshot — this is why the\ndefinitions backup in the pre-upgrade checklist is mandatory. The quorum queue\ncreated in Step 1 is forward-compatible with 3.12, so queue type migration does\nnot itself block rollback.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Risk Summary\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|\n| Classic mirrored queue removed in 4.0 | High | Step 1 (queue migration to quorum) must complete before any 4.0 attempt |\n| `app-producer` failing pre-upgrade confounds validation | Medium | Diagnose and fix before the change window opens |\n| Brief `app-queue` unavailability during queue re-declaration (Step 1) | Medium | Coordinate a quiesce window; drain queue to zero before delete |\n| Feature flag enablement is irreversible (Step 3) | High | Treat Step 3 as the point of no return; confirm rollback window has closed before running it |\n| Erlang 26 behavior differences | Low | No application-level Erlang coupling; risk is framework-internal only |\nPLANEOF\necho \"Written: $(wc -l < /tmp/plan.md) lines\"","description":"Write plan.md to /tmp"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":105,"cache_read_input_tokens":40562,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":105},"output_tokens":51,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"22aadd6e-19b4-4a96-bb35-59be6d64c0a7","uuid":"af52a2e0-0dae-4d58-9d1d-06bcdb4f47fc","request_id":"req_011Cc76Xwv8yqiPHJLTUhMLj"}
