{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01F8W3sZGc1TMRrB9tj3Jevj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `change-plan` ConfigMap is created and verified. The live cluster is untouched. Here's what was found and planned:\n\n**Current state (snapshot):**\n- RabbitMQ **3.12.14** on Erlang 25.3.2.15 — version is out of support\n- 3 vhosts: `/`, `/app`, `/ops`\n- 3 users: `admin` (administrator), `app-user` (management, `/app` only), `ops-user` (management, `/ops` only)\n- 2 classic durable queues: `app-queue` in `/app`, `ops-queue` in `/ops`\n- 1 policy: `ha-all` on `/app` applying `ha-mode:all` + `ha-sync-mode:automatic` — **deprecated and removed in RabbitMQ 4.0**\n- `app-producer` pod is currently in `CrashLoopBackOff`\n\n**Key migration concerns in the plan:**\n1. **`ha-all` classic mirroring policy** must be removed and `app-queue` migrated to a quorum queue before any 4.0 upgrade can be attempted (4.0 removes classic mirroring entirely)\n2. **Upgrade path**: 3.12 → 3.13 (stepping stone) → 4.0, each in a separate change window\n3. **`app-producer` crash** must be diagnosed before the change window to enable post-upgrade validation\n4. **Feature flag enablement** after 3.13 rollout is the irreversible point-of-no-return — rollback is only possible before that step"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":369,"cache_read_input_tokens":44319,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":369},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"22aadd6e-19b4-4a96-bb35-59be6d64c0a7","uuid":"26129170-f4c1-4703-99c7-48d7c2684da8","request_id":"req_011Cc76d4kJ63atavR9z2ioH"}
